                <head>183. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Cuba was discussed under the heading “U.S. Policy Toward Cuba” at the 479th
                    meeting of the National Security Council on April 27, 1961. According to the
                    Record of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Actions, approved by the President
                    on April 29, the following decisions were adopted as <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> Action No. 2413: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“a. Noted the Presidentʼs view that a decision with respect to
                                trading with Cuba should be deferred pending developments in Cuba
                                during the next week.</item>
                            <item>“b. Noted the Presidentʼs request that the Attorney General should
                                prepare recommendations regarding control of Cubans entering or
                                residing in the United States.</item>
                            <item>“c. Noted the Presidentʼs request that Assistant Secretary of
                                Defense <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName>, in
                                consultation with appropriate agencies, should complete the Defense
                                study of the military training of Cubans and coordinate it with
                                further proposals from the Department of State with respect to the
                                broader aspects of the Cuban problem.” (<persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                                    >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, Meetings
                                and Memoranda Series, National Security Council Meetings, No.
                                479)</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>According to the Record of Actions, the following people, in addition to the
                    President were among the participants in the meeting: <persName
                        corresp="#p_KRF1">Robert Kennedy</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DAW1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1">Bissell</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAAA1">Burke</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GRL1"
                        >Gilpatric</persName>, Stahr, Connally, Zuckert, <persName corresp="#p_NPH1"
                        >Nitze</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MER1">Murrow</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BMG2"
                        >McGeorge Bundy</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_STC3">Sorensen</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_GRN2">Goodwin</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="#p_TMD1">Taylor</persName>. (Ibid.)</p>
